'''茉莉花革命'''（{{lang-ar|ثورة الياسمين}}，{{lang-fr|Révolution de jasmin}}），指發生於2010年末至2011年初的[[北非|北非]][[突尼西亞|突尼西亞]]反政府示威導致政權倒台的事件，因[[茉莉花|茉莉花]]是其國花而得名<ref name=wp>{{cite news |first=Mona |last=Eltahawy |title=Tunisia's Jasmine Revolution |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/01/14/AR2011011405084.html |work=[[Washington_Post|Washington Post]] |publisher= |date=2011-01-15 |accessdate=2011-01-15 |archive-date=2011-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110222062734/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/01/14/AR2011011405084.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=ahramonline>{{cite news |first= |last= |title=Tunisia's 'Jasmine Revolution' jolts Arab world |url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/~/NewsContent/2/8/3955/World/Region/Tunisias-Jasmine-Revolution-jolts-Arab-world.aspx |work=[[法新社|法新社]] |publisher=[[Ahram_Online|Ahram Online]] |date=2011-01-15 |accessdate=2011-01-15 |archive-date=2011-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110220024554/http://english.ahram.org.eg/~/NewsContent/2/8/3955/World/Region/Tunisias-Jasmine-Revolution-jolts-Arab-world.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2010年12月17日，一名26歲青年[[穆罕默德·布瓦吉吉|穆罕默德·布瓦吉吉]]（{{lang|ar|محمد البوعزيزي}}，Mohamed Bouazizi）自焚，觸發境内大规模街頭示威游行及争取民主活動。事件導致時任總統[[宰因·阿比丁·本·阿里|本·阿里]]政權倒台<ref name="bbc12195025">{{cite web |author=Wyre Davies |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-12195025 |title=BBC News – Tunisia: President Zine al-Abidine Ben Ali forced out |publisher=BBC |date=2010-12-15 |accessdate=2011-01-14 |archive-date=2016-01-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160123073341/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-12195025 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.indybay.org/newsitems/2011/01/16/18669320.php |title=Uprising in Tunisia: People Power topples Ben Ali regime : Indybay<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2011-01-20 |archive-date=2011-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110726181556/http://www.indybay.org/newsitems/2011/01/16/18669320.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>，成為[[阿拉伯國家|阿拉伯國家]]中第一場因人民起義導致推翻現政權的革命。

突尼西亞歷史上鮮見如此大規模的示威騷亂事件<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2011/01/10/world/main7233191.shtml |title=Deadly Riots in Tunisia Shut Down Schools |publisher=Cbsnews.com |date=2011-01-10 |accessdate=2011-01-15 |archive-date=2013-11-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104062313/http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2011/01/10/world/main7233191.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。事件發生前，各界普遍認為突尼西亞相對鄰近國家是較富裕和穩定的<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/africa/2011/01/2011191414183128.html |title=Protesters killed in Tunisia riots |publisher=English.aljazeera.net |date=2011-01-09 |accessdate=2011-01-15 |archive-date=2011-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106071022/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/africa/2011/01/2011191414183128.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

這起騷亂事件被一些西方媒體稱為「'''西迪布吉德起義'''」（{{rtl-lang|ar|ثورة سيدي بوزيد}}，{{lang|en|Sidi Bouzid Revolt}}）<ref name="SidiBouzid_FB">{{Cite web |url=http://www.facebook.com/video/video.php?v=151395198244689 |title=Niet compatibele browser {{!}} Facebook<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2011-02-04 |archive-date=2013-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130221085654/http://www.facebook.com/video/video.php?v=151395198244689 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="SidiBouzid_libcom">{{Cite web |url=http://libcom.org/forums/news/protests-spread-tunisia-29122010 |title=The Sidi Bouzid Revolution: Ben Ali flees as protests spread in Tunisia {{!}} libcom.org<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2011-02-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121123041523/http://libcom.org/forums/news/protests-spread-tunisia-29122010 |archive-date=2012-11-23 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 及「'''尊嚴革命'''」（{{rtl-lang|ar|ثورة الكرامة}}，{{lang|en|Dignity Revolution}}）。另有人認為一些[[新媒體|新媒體]]將當地情況傳播至各地，有助於推翻本·阿里的政權<ref>Luke Alnutt (2012)[http://www.rferl.org/content/tunisia_can_we_please_stop_talking_about_twitter_revolutions/2277052.html TANGLED WEB Tunisia: Can We Please Stop Talking About 'Twitter Revolutions'?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/tunisia_can_we_please_stop_talking_about_twitter_revolutions/2277052.html |date=20110130180955 }} Accessed on 2011-01-15.</ref><ref name=autogenerated4>{{Cite web |url=http://technosociology.org/?p=263 |title=Tunisia, Twitter, Aristotle, Social Media and Final and Efficient Causes {{!}} technosociology<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2011-01-16 |archive-date=2011-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110117191007/http://technosociology.org/?p=263 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，因此又稱作「[[Twitter|Twitter]]革命」<ref name=fp>{{cite news |first=Marc |last=Lynch |title=Tunisia and the New Arab Media Space |url=http://lynch.foreignpolicy.com/posts/2011/01/15/tunisia_and_the_new_arab_media_space |work=[[外交政策|外交政策]] |publisher= |date=2011-01-15 |accessdate=2011-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711020805/http://lynch.foreignpolicy.com/posts/2011/01/15/tunisia_and_the_new_arab_media_space |archive-date=2011-07-11 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 或「[[WikiLeaks|WikiLeaks]]革命」<ref>{{cite news |first=Elizabeth |last=Dickinson |title=The First WikiLeaks Revolution? |url=http://wikileaks.foreignpolicy.com/posts/2011/01/13/wikileaks_and_the_tunisia_protests |work=[[外交政策|外交政策]] |publisher= |date=2011-01-13 |accessdate=2011-01-15 |archive-date=2011-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110627123123/http://wikileaks.foreignpolicy.com/posts/2011/01/13/wikileaks_and_the_tunisia_protests |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

茉莉花革命對[[北部非洲|北部非洲]]及[[中东|中东]]產生了極大的影響，其示威抗議的模式亦受一些國家的民眾所效法（如[[2010－2011年阿爾及利亞反政府示威|阿爾及利亞]]、[[2011年埃及反政府示威|埃及]]等），导致反政府的示威浪潮在一个月内[[2010－2011年阿拉伯世界反政府浪潮|席卷整个北部非洲与中東地區]]。[[突尼斯|突尼西亞]]此後成立過渡政府，並成為[[阿拉伯之春|阿拉伯之春]]中，唯一達成和平過渡完成民主轉型的國家。

== 背景與起因 ==
[[File:Zine_El_Abidine_Ben_Ali_2.jpg|thumb]]
[[本·阿里|本·阿里]]于1987年發動同樣稱作「茉莉花革命」的不流血政變推翻時任总统[[哈比卜·布尔吉巴|哈比卜·布尔吉巴]]而上臺<ref>{{Lien web|url=http://www.fidh.org/DE-LA-REVOLUTION-DE-JASMIN-A-LA-REVOLUTION-RCD|title=De la révolution de jasmin à la révolution « RCD » (retour à la case départ)|author=[[Fédération_internationale_des_droits_de_l'homme|FIDH]]|date=21 octobre 1999|accessdate=16 janvier 2011|archive-date=2011-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111102173520/http://www.fidh.org/DE-LA-REVOLUTION-DE-JASMIN-A-LA-REVOLUTION-RCD|dead-url=no}}</ref>，此后他在1994年、1999年、2004年和2009年四次连任突尼斯总统。<ref>[http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=tunisia&d=SNAAMA&f=grID:101;currID:USD;pcFlag:1;crID:788 UNdata Record View Per Capita GDP at Current Prices] {{Wayback|url=http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=tunisia&d=SNAAMA&f=grID:101;currID:USD;pcFlag:1;crID:788 |date=20111003095820 }}，United Nations。</ref> 從1987年起的大約20年間，國內生產總值每年平均以接近5%的速度增長。然而2008年的[[金融海嘯|金融海嘯]]導致旅遊業走下坡，[[失業率|失業率]]上升。<ref name="end of an era">{{cite web |author=Hashem Ahelbarra |url=http://blogs.aljazeera.net/2011/01/14/tunisia-end-era |title=Tunisia: The end of an era |publisher=Blogs.aljazeera.net (Al Jazeera Blogs) |date= |accessdate=2011-01-15 |archive-date=2012-03-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120330084315/http://blogs.aljazeera.net/2011/01/14/tunisia-end-era |dead-url=no }}</ref> 在2010年的調查報告指出，突尼西亞的經濟增長率為3.8％，但失業率達14％，其中又有30％是年輕人<ref name=nikkei20110114>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nikkei.com/news/category/article/g=96958A9C9381959FE3E6E2E3EA8DE3E6E2E3E0E2E3E3E2E2E2E2E2E2;at=DGXZZO0195570008122009000000|title=チュニジア大統領、次期選挙に不出馬表明　民主化を約束|newspaper=[[日本経済新聞|日本経済新聞]] 日経電子版|date=2011-01-14|accessdate=2011-01-16|archive-date=2011-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111120081533/http://www.nikkei.com/news/category/article/g=96958A9C9381959FE3E6E2E3EA8DE3E6E2E3E0E2E3E3E2E2E2E2E2E2;at=DGXZZO0195570008122009000000|dead-url=no}}</ref>，另有報導指青年失業率可能高達52%<ref>[http://news.sina.com.hk/news/12/1/1/1985737/1.html 突尼斯騷亂致總統外逃 年輕人失業率高達52%] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110122120709/http://news.sina.com.hk/news/12/1/1/1985737/1.html |date=2011-01-22 }}</ref>。

此外，[[通貨膨脹|通貨膨脹]]、[[政治腐敗|政治腐敗]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Spencer |first=Richard |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/tunisia/8258077/Tunisia-riots-US-warns-Middle-East-to-reform-or-be-overthrown.html |title=Tunisia riots: Reform or be overthrown, US tells Arab states amid fresh riots |publisher=Telegraph |date= |accessdate=2011-01-14 |archive-date=2011-04-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110428093924/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/tunisia/8258077/Tunisia-riots-Reform-or-be-overthrown-US-tells-Arab-states-amid-fresh-riots.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[言論自由|言論缺乏自由]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Ryan |first=Yasmine |url=http://english.aljazeera.net/indepth/features/2011/01/20111614145839362.html |title=Tunisia's bitter cyberwar |publisher=Al Jazeera English |date= |accessdate=2011-01-14 |archive-date=2011-10-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111031214738/http://english.aljazeera.net/indepth/features/2011/01/20111614145839362.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 及[[貧窮|生活條件不佳]]也是造成此事件的主要原因之一。还有研究表明，小麦生产和消费方面均居世界首位的中国在2010年遭遇严重干旱，导致[[小麦|小麦]]歉收而不得不依赖进口，引发小麦价格暴涨。而埃及是世界最大小麦进口国，粮食价格的暴涨也是引发人们走上街头的诱因之一<ref>{{cite web | author =  | title = 中国谷物歉收动摇国际政治？ | publisher = 日经中文网 | date = 2013-05-08 | url = http://cn.nikkei.com/politicsaeconomy/politicsasociety/5476-20130508.html | doi =  | id =  | access-date = 2013-05-08 | archive-date = 2020-10-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029042813/https://cn.nikkei.com/politicsaeconomy/politicsasociety/5476-20130508.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

除了上述的民生問題之外，還有一些原因來自於[[網際網路|網際網路]]。2010年12月，[[WikiLeaks|維基解密]]揭露2009年6月的美國外交電文，內容為引述當時美國駐突尼斯大使Robert Godec的報告，指出指突尼斯是「警察國家」，本·阿里家族及其兄弟手足與掌管該國經濟的一名黑道份子勾結，並指第一夫人[[勒伊拉澤魯·本·阿里|勒伊拉澤魯·本·阿里]]（ليلى بن علي，Lelia Ben Ali）靠興建貴族學校賺取利益<ref>{{fr}} Séréni, Jean-Pierre. [http://www.monde-diplomatique.fr/carnet/2011-01-06-Tunisie "Le réveil tunisien"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.monde-diplomatique.fr/carnet/2011-01-06-Tunisie |date=20210323170720 }} ''Le Monde Diplomatique''. January 6, 2011. Retrieved January 13, 2011.</ref><ref name="rage">Kirkpatrick, David D. [http://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/14/world/africa/14tunisia.html?ref=africa Behind Tunisia Unrest, Rage Over Wealth of Ruling Family] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/14/world/africa/14tunisia.html?ref=africa |date=20170615105038 }}. ''New York Times''. January 13, 2011. Retrieved January 13, 2011.</ref>。揭露外交電文後加深了民眾對於政府不滿的情緒，而這起揭露事件也成為騷亂爆發的重要導火線之一<ref>{{cite web | language = zh-cn | publisher = 中工网 | title = 突尼斯社会动荡加剧 | url = http://world.workercn.cn/c/2011/01/13/110113054738164751068.html | date = 2011-01-13 | accessdate = 2011-01-13 | archive-date = 2018-09-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180929034959/http://world.workercn.cn/c/2011/01/13/110113054738164751068.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

=== 穆罕默德·布瓦吉吉自焚 ===
整起事件起因是發生在该国南部城市[[西迪布吉德|西迪布吉德]]，一位26岁青年[[穆罕默德·布瓦吉吉|穆罕默德·布瓦吉吉]]拉著一部攤車在街上販賣蔬菜水果，但因為沒有申請擺攤執照而被警察部门沒收攤車<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-12120228 Tunisia suicide protester Mohammed Bouazizi dies] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-12120228 |date=20110124022249 }}, BBC, January 5, 2011.</ref>。不久之後，他因為抗議警察執法而于2010年12月17日自焚<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com/news/world/article/922279--suicide-protest-helped-topple-tunisian-regime|title=Suicide protest helped topple Tunisian regime|access-date=2011-01-20|archive-date=2011-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110118071140/http://www.thestar.com/news/world/article/922279--suicide-protest-helped-topple-tunisian-regime|dead-url=no}}</ref>，導致一連串反政府的示威抗議正式開始並逐漸擴散至全國。

2011年1月4日，因為自焚而送去醫院急救的穆罕默德·布瓦吉吉不治身亡<ref>{{cite web |url=http://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFJOE70408420110105 |title=Tunisian who sparked rare protests dies: relatives -Reuters |publisher=Af.reuters.com |date=2011-01-05 |accessdate=2011-01-14 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303213146/http://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFJOE70408420110105 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

== 早期的示威抗議 ==
[[File:Tunisia_Unrest_-_VOA_-_Tunis_14_Jan_2011_(2).jpg|thumb]]的街道進行示威抗議]]
布瓦吉吉自焚之後，數百名年輕的抗議者在西迪布吉德進行示威，並聚集在市府大樓前。警察則使用催淚瓦斯進行驅趕，而[[社交網路服務|社交網站]][[Facebook|Facebook]]及[[YouTube|YouTube]]上已經有人將警察與示威民眾發生衝突的影片上傳。12月19日，當局已經調來更多警察在西迪布吉德街頭維持秩序<ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/africa/2010/12/2010122063745828931.html|title=Images posted on social-network sites show police intervening to halt disturbances ignored by national media|date=20 December 2010|work=[[Al_Jazeera|Al Jazeera]]|accessdate=20 December 2010|archive-date=2011-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110408171358/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/africa/2010/12/2010122063745828931.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

12月22日，一位名叫拉漢森·納吉的抗議者表示自己受夠了「飢餓和失業」，於是爬上[[電塔|電塔]]並使自己觸電<ref name="Protests continue in Tunisia">{{cite news|url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/africa/2010/12/2010122682433751904.html|title=Protests continue in Tunisia|date=26 December 2010|work=[[Al_Jazeera|Al Jazeera]]|accessdate=26 December 2010|archive-date=2011-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110207082919/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/africa/2010/12/2010122682433751904.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
